## Step 1: Understand what constitutes net profit
Net profit is typically calculated as total revenue minus all expenses, including:
- Cost of goods sold
- Operating expenses (administrative, sales expenses)
- Financial expenses
- Depreciation
- Tax (if applicable)

## Step 2: Extract all revenue from sales
I'll identify all sales transactions and sum up the profit values.

All sales have a type of "Sale" and include a "profit" column that shows the profit from each sale.
